A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. 1 To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs 'Wonder Woman' Gal Gadot welcomes baby daughter Maya Maeve McDermott , USATODAY 4:44 p.m. ET March 20, 2017 Congratulations are in order for Gal Gadot. (Photo: Steve Granitz, WireImage) 
Wonder Woman Gal Gadot just welcomed her own superhero-in-training to the family. 
The 31-year-old actress and husband Yaron Versano announced the birth of their second daughter, Maya, with a happy (and pun-filled) Instagram post Monday. 
"And then we were four... She is here, Maya. I feel so complete blessed and thankful for all the Wonders in my life," the new mom, who first announced her pregnancy in November 2016 , wrote in the caption. 
After co-starring in last year's Batman vs. Superman , the actress' standalone Wonder Woman movie hits theaters on June 2. A post shared by Gal Gadot (@gal_gadot) on Mar 20, 2017 at 11:43am PDT 
On Sunday, Gadot shared a snap of her nine-months-pregnant belly. A post shared by Gal Gadot (@gal_gadot) on Mar 19, 2017 at 6:24pm PDT 
Gadot and Versano welcomed their first daughter Alma in 2011. 
Gal Gadot showed off her baby bump at the 2017 Golden Globe Awards. (Photo: Steve Granitz)
